# CiberC-LG

SDK for Lighting Gale Cimcon that expose a client to platform.

This package use [ZoneInfo](https://docs.python.org/3/library/zoneinfo.html), python 3.9+ is required or install for compatibility
[backports](https://pypi.org/project/backports.zoneinfo/)

## Use

```python
from lg import LGApi, LGAuth, TokenCache, TokenFileStorage

# Optional, create an implementation of cache for token.
# You can use TokenFileStorage or leave as None.
MyCacheToken(TokenCache):
"""Implements a cache for the token"""


...
my_cache = MyCacheToken(...)  # Optional
lg_auth = LGAuth(username, password, base_url, ssl_verify=False, token_cache=my_cache)
lg_api - LGApi(lg_auth)
...
```

## Changes

- [v071] LGApi fix access_token
- [v070] Add TokenCache abstract class.
- [v060] BREAKING CHANGE: Create a shortcut get_all_slc_with_data and remove method get_all_slc.
- [v051] Pydantic v2 support and fix Optional typing with default value

[v044]

- Add Exception module
- get_all_slc_data supports StatusError

- [v043] LG Auth add logger parameter for logger disable InsecureRequestWarning
- [v042] Method dim_slc, param value add support to str int float

[v034]

- Change Model for SwitchOnOff to CommandData and CommandResponse
- Implement dimmer set

[v033]

- rename method getLatitudeLongitudeSLC as get_latitude_longitude_slc
- StatusParameters add description

[v032]

- Fix SLCData add alias
- Fix typo in var names

- [v031] Fix setup include subpackage lg/models
